rComments: There are limited opportunities to do well in class, so you need to be prepared for the two midterms and final essay. There's an excessive amount of reading, but Dr. Brownfield gives you the tools to succeed on the tests and essay. He's very soft spoken, but is very knowledgable. You should be able to do well if you can commit to taking good notes.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: BASED BROWNFIELD BEST PROF MATERIAL CLEAR STRAIGHTFORWARD GPA WENT 0 to 100 REAL QUICK

He tends to mumble during his lectures, but he's very nice and approachable so don't be afraid to ask for clarification. He's the fairest professor I've ever had at UTM. He tells you exactly what to expect on the tests and describes in detail what he expects in your papers. The material is straightforward. I took two of his courses and aced both.

Overall great professor really straight forward with tests and assignments. Simple attend the lecture do the reading you'll end up doing great. You can't go wrong with David Brownfield, simply great individual and professor.
Hard to understand him, he mumbles, everyone would always fall asleep during his lectures.

He's not as hard to understand as people make him out to be. Yes, he mumbles sometimes but still very understandable and more than happy to repeat if you need clarification. Very approachable prof. Tests are very fair (tells you what to expect), although MC is tricky. Wished he would've given the rubric for the essay though. Good prof overall.
very nice professor but he is hard to understand because he talks so quietly. Really easy assignment and fair midterms. Tells you exactly what kind of questions to expect for the tests
Ok course, with an extremely well rounded prof.
One of the best professor I've ever had. Talks in a very low tone but is very clear. Assignment was very easy and so was the mid-term and in-class final.
I enjoyed his class. Talks in really low tone, sometimes hard to understand but overall he is a good prof. He knows his subject well and always available to answer any questions.

I cannot STAND his mumbling. I can't understand a word he says, he teaches as if he's talking to himself rather than an entire class. He may be an easy prof, but he can't teach at all. His voice is definitely not the first thing I wanna hear at 10am on a Friday.

Best Prof EVER! Ace'd my fourth year seminar class, and.... got a PIZZA PARTY at the end of the semester. didnt use the textbook, had a lot to talk about (not course related), very interesting! also does a lot of not for profit fundraiser stuff... overall favorite prof at UTM

He is CRAZY. (Not sure if that's a good or a bad thing) I actually thought he was on something. Super loopy. Nice guy, but kinda gives me the creeps! Super interesting course though. He really knows his stuff, and is very helpful.

Brownfield is HILARIOUS!!! His lectures were always a source of entertainment. If you put in the effort, you can really thrive in the class. the best thing about Brownfield is that he is very approachable and helpful,talk to him and you'll be glad you did

Best prof. ever. Clear as day, easy to understand, makes class interesting. (211 was a bit boring but 307 was awesome...smaller class). His power points and to the point and his assignments and tests are fair and understandable. Great prof. at UTM. Outstanding.
dull, monotone, and flat out ridiculous.....i would rather stare at a fuzzy television screen for a whole day then try to listen to him

Prof. B is quite possibly the greatest professor @ UTM. Very helpful & going to his classes will pay off, believe me! I'm an ECO major and Prof. B. actually sat down & gave me positive feedback about my future goals and how to get there. Just an all around GR8 person & a class act! Very approachable with organized and helpful lectures!SOC211/SOC307
By far the best prof I've ever had.  He's so approachable and really offers positive comments towards his students, which is rare among profs.  I highly recommend taking his course!

he could make the material more interesting- entire course revolves around measuring crime- u will come across 1000 stats in this course & learn 1000 studies- class average on test 2 was 60- his tests questions are hard & specific- they are marked hard- lectures are boring- talk faster & speak louder- best thing about the course - the TA
This is the 2nd time I have had him. Me and my friends all love him! Hes such a good teacher easy to understand and reallllly helpful. He's got to be my favorite prof so far.

Pleasant and clam approach to teaching/learning that involves an indepth analysis of the material without being condescending.  Exams involve serious memorization but he narrows the subject area down well to assist students.

One of the best profs at UTM. One 1.5 hour lecture a week that is very well organized and clear. He goes slow and explains everything clearly. He gives very generous hints for tests and is very approachable and friendly, unlike....say...Kirk Blankstein
Prof Brownfield is awesome! He spells out each point in lectures SO clearly, and is a funny guy! I really recommend his classes!
Talk faster!

Lectures can be boring at times, but he's extremely knowledgable, all you have to do is ask.  Tests are fair, multiple choice is hard and the essay isn't too difficult...great prof.
